Many astro photography images on @apod are copyrighted. If you want to use them in a talk  email copyright owner & ask - R.Nemiroff #CAP2016
What makes a good @apod image? Good images of the sky where you can use a rollover to show constellations & stuff - R.Nemiroff #CAP2016 6/n
What makes a good @apod image? One that uses multiple planes: foreground  background  sky  humans + astro objects - R.Nemiroff #CAP2016 5/n
What makes a good @apod image? Could be also very simple: eg. the average colour of the universe was very popular - R.Nemiroff #CAP2016 4/n
What makes a good @apod image? One that tells a story & triggers qst: eclipse  @MarsCuriosity rover at Red Planet - R.Nemiroff #CAP2016 3/n
What makes a good @apod image? Topical image  eg. @LIGO gravitational waves  unusually published later in the day - R.Nemiroff #CAP2016 2/n
What makes a good @apod image? Some are immediately awe inspiring eg. dazzling aurorae  Earthrise from Moon - R.Nemiroff #CAP2016 1/n
At @apod they try to communicate at different levels: kids  students & teachers at all levels  science literates & non  prof astros #CAP2016
